  "name": "Vocal Membrane",
  "mood": "Aether",
  "engines": [
    "Obrix"
  ],
  "description": "Vocal wavetable bank (wtBank=2) with proc1 as LP at 660 Hz — the center of the vowel formant zone — with resonance 0.30, the sweet spot where the filter whispers rather than screams. Coprime LFOs: 0.13 Hz modulates wtPos (the wavetable scans through vowel shapes), 0.17 Hz modulates cutoff1 (the formant peak breathes). The result is a membrane — a biological acoustic interface between inside and outside. Not a voice, but the tissue that makes voice possible.",
